comments[17]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T20:44:47.549Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start: bundled with pm-zwpp, pm-oxrw, pm-m4iu, pm-cbwg, pm-w89s, and pm-usfg. Live duplicate/context check found no closed schema/config/profile SDK primitive completion; prior read/lifecycle/package primitives remain separate shipped or in-progress domains."
  "2026-07-07T22:45:27.701Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: post-review docs/API cleanup keeps package authors on the correct context-management primitive shapes: linked file/doc adds use string arrays and top-level note, while SchemaResult documents the generic schema customization result union. Verified through docs gate, typecheck, focused SDK tests, and packed installed SDK proof."
  "2026-07-07T23:52:21.378Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: the generic SDK schema() return type now explicitly includes all concrete inspect results as well as schema mutation results, preserving compile-time safety for customization primitive consumers. Focused SDK test and full coverage passed."
  "2026-07-08T00:36:44.011Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: schemaShow, schemaShowField, schemaShowStatus, profileShow, and profileLint now pass their name positional as a top-level SDK action property, matching the established SDK command wrapper convention used by other positional helpers."
  "2026-07-08T06:06:35.974Z",codex,"Evidence: context-management SDK primitives remain covered by full coverage and installed-package proof; lifecycle shortcuts now expose typed composed result contracts so agent/package authors can consume claim/update/close/release payloads without unknown casts."
  "2026-07-11T23:05:01.192Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: selected after live all-status duplicate checks, full metadata/comments/notes/learnings review, GitHub issue/PR/security/dependency inspection, and SDK-first frontier reconciliation. This item is actively edited in the broad schema/config/profile/init SDK promotion bundle; unrelated open items remain unclaimed."
  "2026-07-11T23:15:37.998Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence: promoted workspace cache scaffolding into a typed public SDK primitive consumed by pm init, documented and packed-consumer tested. The broader schema/config/profile/init command-to-core extraction remains open; this PR does not claim full pm-3mna completion."
  "2026-07-12T08:31:32.782Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: active wide SDK bundle promotes schema mutation orchestration behind typed public primitives after the runtime dispatch decomposition; live blockers pm-lodl and pm-muhw are closed with shipped evidence."
  "2026-07-12T09:50:10.298Z",codex-root,"Scope reconciliation: no schema mutation primitive implementation landed in this branch; item returned to open so only actively delivered annotation work remains completed/in review."
  "2026-07-14T19:24:55.099Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: live full-tracker/all-status and GitHub reconciliation selected the schema domain extraction as the broad SDK-first lane. This run will move schema primitive/types ownership out of src/cli, make CLI registration a presentation adapter, update public SDK docs/tests, and preserve behavior."
  "2026-07-14T19:40:59.373Z",codex-gpt5,"Progress evidence: schema inspection/mutation ownership now lives in src/sdk/schema.ts; the CLI module is a compatibility re-export and SDK runtime imports schema primitives directly. Focused schema/SDK tests, 100% docstring static gate, package boundary, token budget, docs/skills, and governed contract checks pass."
  "2026-07-14T20:19:47.964Z",codex-root,"Final branch evidence: schema inspection/mutation ownership moved from the CLI into src/sdk/schema.ts; the CLI is now a compatibility re-export and SDK runtime/MCP consume the SDK-owned engine. The import-boundary ratchet removed 17 schema edges, stale suppressions were deleted, and the hard suppression budget fell 174 -> 170. Exact verification on the final source: 290 files / 5,701 tests; 36,848/36,848 statements, 26,463/26,463 branches, 7,438/7,438 functions, 35,963/35,963 lines; typecheck, strict lint, zero-clone, 100% module/export/member docstrings, package boundary, token budget, docs, contracts, security, version, packed npm smoke, 88-command dogfood, and fresh external PmClient schema/custom-type lifecycle all pass. Broader config/profile/init implementation ownership remains for this feature, so it returns to open."
  "2026-07-14T20:44:53.761Z",codex-root,"PR #563 round-1 review: accepted both CodeRabbit maintainability findings. runSchemaAddType and loadSchemaInspectionContext now share ensureInitialized; all eight mutation results use finalizeWarnings for stable dedupe/sort. Focused schema/init/MCP tests, typecheck, static quality, and exact 100/100/100/100 coverage pass. The CodeRabbit external docstring heuristic warning is contradicted by the repository's mandatory 100% module/export/member docstring gate, which remains green."
  "2026-07-14T22:56:34.037Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-15: live 1,834-item all-status tracker, full item comments/notes/learnings/dependency graph, and GitHub PR/issue/security/dependency state were reconciled. This broad lane completes config/profile/init SDK ownership after schema, preserves CLI behavior, updates docs/tests/boundary ratchets, and includes packed temp-consumer proof."
  "2026-07-14T23:44:00.374Z",unknown,"Verification evidence 2026-07-15: final all-source coverage passed 291 files / 5,708 tests at exact 100% (36,925 statements, 26,508 branches, 7,449 functions, 36,040 lines). Release readiness also passed build/typecheck, docs/skills, 100% module/export/member docstrings, package boundary, token budgets, version policy, secret scan, packed npx smoke, and 88-command package-first dogfood. The aggregate gate stops only on pre-existing external Sentry highs PM-CLI-2B/pm-d4ns and PM-CLI-29/pm-7n5a; telemetry is healthy at 0.34% finish errors with zero missing error-code rows."
  "2026-07-15T01:07:24.059Z",codex-root,"PR #565 round-1 hardening and acceptance evidence: accepted actionable Greptile/CodeRabbit findings for scoped history validation, strict global author parsing, exact config integer validation, atomic guidance writes, pre-mutation init validation, resolved-workspace guidance, and fixture fidelity. Promoted the extension lifecycle engine into SDK ownership when review exposed the remaining init-to-CLI boundary. Final exact all-source gate: 291 files / 5,713 tests; 36,940/36,940 statements, 26,521/26,521 branches, 7,450/7,450 functions, 36,055/36,055 lines. Strict lint, 100% module/export/member docstrings, package boundary, token budget, zero clones, contracts, and static ratchets pass. Fresh packed-tarball temp consumer installed all 12 aliases, initialized a real tracker with persistent author_default, created/commented with invocation overrides, validated zero history drift/unknown authors, managed 11 unique extensions, and imported the SDK-owned CLI program/scanner/extension engine successfully."
  "2026-07-15T01:16:44.305Z",codex-root,"Greptile pre-push review completed on commit 2093506c at confidence 5/5, safe to merge, with no review comments. It verified the SDK extraction as behavior-preserving through compatibility re-exports, strict non-greedy author parsing, try/finally environment restoration, and history-drift-scoped advisory diagnostics."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T17:32:56.449Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation slicing 2026-07-10 (grounded in current src state). Already public — do NOT redo: profile read-side (presets/plan/describe/lint exported via src/sdk/index.ts), schema runtime registries (resolveRuntimeFieldRegistry/resolveRuntimeStatusRegistry via src/sdk/runtime.ts), and generic PmClient.runTyped wrappers for the schema/config/profile/init actions. The actual gap: domain logic lives in CLI command modules — src/cli/commands/schema.ts (1973 lines), config.ts (1576), init.ts (955) + init-agent-guidance.ts (566), ~5.1k lines total — so SDK consumers reach these domains only through generic action dispatch, not typed primitives. Suggested slices: S1 schema mutation primitives (~150m) — extract add-type/add-field/status-def write paths into src/core/schema (fields-file/item-types-file/status-defs-file already own the file formats); command becomes parse+render. S2 config/settings primitives (~90m) — extract read/write/validate onto src/core/config/nested-settings; preserve the settings validator's unknown-key-stripping semantics (PR#314). S3 init + workspace-discovery primitive (~90m) — single source of truth for discovery; this is where the GH-501/pm-69nl class (init target invisible to discovery) gets fixed at the primitive level — coordinate with pm-69nl, do not duplicate its fix. S4 typed PmClient facades + SDK reference docs/tests (~60m) — replace generic payloads with typed inputs/outputs; each primitive must match the equivalent runAction result shape (semantics oracle, pm-usfg 07-06 note). Order: S1 first (schema gates the pm-w89s universality story); S2/S3 independent; S4 last."
  "2026-07-12T06:11:44.315Z",maintainer-agent,"Adjacent ship, scope intact: PR#520 (2026-07-12) promoted the FIRST workspace-customization primitive through the public SDK (ensurePmGitignore/getPmGitignoreBlock in src/sdk/workspace.ts) and made init consume it — proof the init-adjacent SDK boundary works end-to-end (packed-tarball external-consumer proof in PR verification). This does NOT deliver S1: schema/config/profile/init command families are still CLI-owned. Use src/sdk/workspace.ts as the pattern exemplar when starting S1."
  "2026-07-12T08:43:59.620Z",codex-root,"Execution rule from user escalation (23rd recurrence): this active delivery lane must not stop at partial implementation, local verification, commit, PR creation, pending checks, or pending bot review. Continue through the requested green reviewed PR, merge, merged-head/release/Sentry/telemetry proof, tracker closure, claim release, and return to main; only a genuine exhausted blocker permits stopping."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T20:19:48.566Z",codex-root,"Moving a CLI command engine into the SDK must also migrate its lint baseline, residual test mocks, and runtime imports; keeping a tiny CLI re-export preserves compatibility while the SDK becomes the single implementation owner."
